## Text tools

Here on macOS grep, sed, and awk (among others) are the BSD-derived versions,
but I usually have the GNU versions installed as ggrep, gsed, and gawk -- in
case you need the GNU enhancements.

{{- end }}

{{- if eq .chezmoi.os "windows" }}

## Windows File Paths

Always use backslashes (`\`) not forward slashes in file paths for the
Read/Edit/Write tools.

- ❌ `"D:/repos/project/file.tsx"`
- ❌ `"/d/repos/project/file.tsx"`
- ✅ `"D:\repos\project\file.tsx"`

{{- end }}

## Mid-turn text is silently lost (Claude Code narration bug)

Claude Code currently suffers from a server-side bug (the "narration" beta;
anthropics/claude-code #65620 has the full analysis) where mid-turn assistant
prose -- any text block other than the turn-opening one right after a typed
user message and the turn-final one -- is emitted as an encrypted `narration`
block instead of a text block. It is neither displayed nor persisted to the
transcript (verified 11/11 lost with claude-fable-5 on 2.1.205, 2026-07-09;
client-side mitigations do not work). Until this is fixed, act as if I never
see any mid-turn text:

- Make the final, turn-ending message self-contained: restate any answers,
  findings, or explanations for tool use that you produced earlier in the turn,
  even though you already "said" them mid-turn.
- Never emit explanatory text followed by AskUserQuestion (or any other tool
  call) mid-turn. Instead, end the turn on the text, asking the question (and
  choices, if applicable) in regular text; I'm happy to answer without the
  tool. This temporarily overrides the AskUserQuestion preference above: still
  ask the questions, just not with the tool.
